From 681d82cc2bc03a16cacb4b12272507e44a1c0b66 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 04:09:44 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 15/39] WIP: media: meson-demux: fix wrong demux2 IRQ number
 (SPI 21 vs 53)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

INT_DEMUX_2 was incorrectly defined as AM_IRQ(21) which maps to GIC
SPI 21 — the same interrupt used by the i2c_A controller. This caused
a genirq flags mismatch and probe failure. The Amlogic vendor kernel
uses AM_IRQ(53) for INT_DEMUX_2. Restore the correct value.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/platform/amlogic/meson-demux/aml_dvb_reg.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/amlogic/meson-demux/aml_dvb_reg.h b/drivers/media/platform/amlogic/meson-demux/aml_dvb_reg.h
index 21ccb34506ef..7c2bdf777af5 100644
--- a/drivers/media/platform/amlogic/meson-demux/aml_dvb_reg.h
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/amlogic/meson-demux/aml_dvb_reg.h
@@ -32,7 +32,7 @@ long aml_stb_get_base(int id);
 #define AM_IRQ(reg) (reg + BASE_IRQ)
 #define INT_DEMUX AM_IRQ(23)
 #define INT_DEMUX_1 AM_IRQ(5)
-#define INT_DEMUX_2 AM_IRQ(21) //AM_IRQ(53)
+#define INT_DEMUX_2 AM_IRQ(53)
 #define INT_ASYNC_FIFO_FILL AM_IRQ(18)
 #define INT_ASYNC_FIFO_FLUSH AM_IRQ(19)
 #define INT_ASYNC_FIFO2_FILL AM_IRQ(24)
-- 
